Readme file:

Terraform AWS VPC and EC2 Cluster
This Terraform code creates an Amazon Web Services (AWS) Virtual Private Cloud (VPC) and an EC2 cluster with two instances, a load balancer, and security groups.

Usage
Clone the repository and navigate to the directory:

bash
Copy code
git clone https://github.com/amit-asman/terraform-aws-vpc-ec2-cluster.git
cd terraform-aws-vpc-ec2-cluster
Modify the variables.tf file to customize the VPC and EC2 cluster settings.

Initialize Terraform and download the required providers:

csharp
Copy code
terraform init
Preview the resources that will be created:

Copy code
terraform plan
Apply the Terraform configuration to create the resources:

Copy code
terraform apply
Resources Created
This Terraform code creates the following resources:

VPC with public subnets and NAT gateways
Security groups for the EC2 instances and load balancer
Two EC2 instances with the specified AMI, instance type, security group, and user data
Application load balancer with a listener and target group
Author
This Terraform code was written by Amit Asman.

